ote. I’m also reflecting on the Native Image and how to clean up the @TempDir, since it contains files like LOCK and LOG. If the static initialization of `JniDBFactory` happens before the test, it could affect loading. I think I might need a dedicated `LibraryTest` for clarity, even if there's no need to import the Library. Plus, I must remember to address any untracked files and metadata edits!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- Added `tests/src/org.fusesource.leveldbjni/leveldbjni-all/1.8/src/test/java/org_fusesource_leveldbjni/leveldbjni_all/LibraryTest.java`\n  - Opens a temporary LevelDB database via `JniDBFactory.factory.open(...)`\n  - Performs a real `put`/`get` round trip\n  - This should drive `NativeDB.LIBRARY.load()`, causing `org.fusesource.hawtjni.runtime.Library` to look up the bundled native library resource through `ClassLoader#getResource(...)`\n\n- Removed the placeholder test:\n  - `Leveldbjni_allTest.java`\n\nI did not run tests, per the workflow instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a9d74a996958a30016a4137529d808190be890724c8d5f088\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 416, "output": 564, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32212, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782658889975, "responseId": "resp_0a9d74a996958a30016a41374a8c1881908fb3863d7397b397"}, "toolResults": []}
